Package edu.cmu.cs214.hw5.framework.core

Interface Framework

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameworkImpl
    public interface Framework
    The Generalized Regression Analysis Framework (GRAF) facilitates the analysis and visualization of country-based, time-series data sets.

    The framework uses three types of plugins: the DataPlugin, which provides the framework with the data set in the generalized form of a RawDataSet; the ModelPlugin, which provides the framework with a forecasting model for predicting future values; and the DisplayPlugin, which gives the framework a visualization of the data in the form of a JPanel.

    The framework admits data sets which associate countries with time-series data that may have multiple attributes.

      • selectDataPlugin

        void selectDataPlugin​(int pluginIndex)
        Selects a registered DataPlugin to be the current active data source during setup. The plugin is specified by its position in the list returned by getDataPluginNames().
        Parameters:
        pluginIndex - index of the desired DataPlugin in the list returned by getDataPluginNames().

      • selectModelPlugin

        void selectModelPlugin​(int pluginIndex)

        pluginIndex - index of the desired ModelPlugin in the list returned by getModelPluginNames().

      • getDataPluginRequiredParameters

        java.util.List<java.lang.String> getDataPluginRequiredParameters()
        Gets the names of the parameters required by the selected DataPlugin. May be an empty list if the selected DataPlugin requires no parameters. The names of the parameters are determine by the plugin.
        Returns:
        a possibly empty list of DataPlugin parameter names.

      • setDataPluginParameters

        boolean setDataPluginParameters​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> parameters)
        Sets the parameters for the selected DataPlugin as the input String to String map. The client should ensure that the keys of this map exactly equal the values in the list returned by getDataPluginRequiredParameters().
        Parameters:
        parameters - Map of parameter names to parameter values (in String form).
        Returns:
        true if the input parameters are complete and well formatted, false otherwise.

      • setModelPluginIncrement

        void setModelPluginIncrement​(ModelPlugin.PredictionIncrement predictionIncrement)
        Sets the time increment between predictions generated by the model plugin. This should match the time increment between data points in the input data set for accurate prediction.
        Parameters:
        predictionIncrement - ModelPlugin.PredictionIncrement between predictions.

      • visualize

        void visualize()
        Visualizes the chosen data set with the chosen regression model through the chosen visualization method. Requires that selectDataPlugin(int), selectDisplayPlugin(int), selectModelPlugin(int), setDataPluginParameters(Map), setModelPluginIncrement(ModelPlugin.PredictionIncrement) have already been successfully called (i.e. initial set up has been completed).
